Good to know thank you!
On Oct 23, 2012 8:14 PM, "Lee Hart" <leeahart@earthlink.net> wrote:

> On 10/23/2012 6:13 PM, Kiff Wilson wrote:
> > Can I use my high current charger until about 80 percent charged and then
> > switch to individual chargers for the last 20 percent and avoid
> > overcharging and undercharging?
>
> Yes. I've even done it! :-)
>
> It's actually a pretty effective way to do it. In my case, I have a
> "dumb" onboard charger that gets the pack up to 80-100% SOC. I then have
> my Battery Balancer, that finished charging each battery individually.
> The Balancer has one small "smart" charger to do the finish charging,
> with a set of relays that selects each battery, one at a time. This
> minimizes the amount of hardware needed.
>
> But it could also be done with a lot of "smart" small chargers. The
> problem with this approach has been discussed earlier; the cost of all
> these smart little chargers is probably more than one big smart charger.
> Plus, there are reliability problems unless these little chargers are
> very reliable.
>
> --
> *BE* the change that you wish to see in the world. -- Mahatma Gandhi
